This paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as sentence segmentation and pronunciation recovery, which are typically categorized under the arXiv sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a deep learning model that utilizes n-gram embeddings and self-attention modules, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and deep learning research (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of semi-supervised learning, which is a technique used to improve model performance with limited labeled data, and is relevant to the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
